caption: Visited 3/27/21. We ordered margaritas and the chicken enchiladas. For having ample amount of workers and the fact that we were sitting close to the bar service was super slow, in regards to arrival of the food as well as the attentiveness of our waiter. Food was bland. I got the enchiladas with the red sauce instead of the green in hopes that it would be spicy but it wasn’t even remotely spicy and tastes kind of like a barbecue sauce, not what I expected. That might have been how they’re intended to taste but wasn’t at all the taste I was hoping and expecting. We also ordered a margarita to go and our waiter brings it in a regular glass and just hands us a plastic cup. Couldn’t he have just put it in the plastic cup to begin with so we didn’t have to fumble around pouring it in the plastic cup ourselves?  I will not be back.

Good drinks and friendly and good service! Was first time there but will go back

20 minutes late on their provided specified pickup time. Food decent, but $11 gets you a pathetically small guacamole portion & the tacos are tiny for the price.

The outdoor dining area is beautiful and feels well spaced out.  There’s a tent and space heaters which go really well with a spicy pineapple margarita which has a really nice kick!  Friendly staff and a great ambience for a drink and some chips and salsa!

Pretty disappointed, the pozole price was different on Uber eats, it’s said it came with tostadas which it didn’t and I ordered three of the pozole. It was pretty much a little bit of chicken and hominey and a ton of broth. For the cost of the meals I was expecting more. The taste was pretty bland and definitely not authentic at all.
Great food
I ordered here from today. There were no onions on one of my tacos. I specifically asked to add onions. The meat was a bit dry but I’d eat it again if I had to.

What a great authentic Mexican restaurant, real food and not to be confused with Tex-Mex, please. Great patio seating area in the heart of Bethesda with individual heaters keep you toasty and safely distant these cold months. Waitstaff are excellent serving killer Margaritas and a good selection of Mexican beers accompany a varied and interesting menu.

Great food, Amazing drinks, mezcal and patio. Love this place. Will be coming back soon.

The food smells great and all, but the tacos are not worth 5$. You can get 2 tacos for 5$ at taco bell and they'd be more filling. And the side of rice was only 1 cups worth, barely enough to put on one taco.. a 13$ meal worth 5$ anywhere else...
Drinks and food are good. The servers are very nice. They should improve on serving the food quicker.

I ordered online . I got the shrimp taco with ranch avocado and cabbage slaw. 2 big shrimp and I got the the three chicken taco and I ask them to add sour cream and guacamole. This place is always packed and I see why. This place is the best place to go to for tacos. The food was so fresh and taste delicious. Presentation is everything and they nailed it and whoever in that kitchen thank you so much because since this pandemic I've been to alot of restaurants and they all disappointed me so , great job and that's why you all are busy with people coming all day everyday.
Chilaquiles were A1! Good vibe and good bottomless mimosas

Delicious food, yummy drinks, friendly service and a great Covid friendly outdoor space. I felt normal! Such a pleasure. Also, dog friendly, which I love. If I lived nearby I would be there at least once a week.
Great COVID safe WARM outdoor seating, good service, great skinny margarita and good food. Limited vegetarian options, but enjoyed the mushroom tacos!
Great food and nice place to sit.
Good food (bit expensive for small portions), good service (bit slow, but very friendly), love the atmosphere and go fairly often.
O.M.G... Haven't had tacos this good since i left L.A.... Highly recommend
Food was excellent, service superb and overall a great value.

It’s what you would expect Mexican food to taste like in Bethesda. If you understand what that means, then trust me this place is not for you lol. Food was pretty bland. Prices are not worth it considering the blandness of the food. If you were to ask me what they made their salsa with, I would have no idea what to say, because of how little flavor there was. The service was SUPER SLOW. I give three stars only because the outside area is cute.
Upon trying them a couple more times, i can say “not bad!”. Food is pricey but very decent, tasty and filling. Good job Casa Oaxaca!
Lovely place. I asked if I could have a quesadilla with corn tortilla instead of flour, and they made it for me! It was delicious. Also their guacamole is on point.

Where should I start....  The service is so bad it shouldn’t even get a star  1- the waiter has no type of customer service. Never asked for napkins, water or it’s the food good. Poor service at all time high  2 - the food is basic. I have Mexican family and they would laugh.  So if you going there, just know that service will be last thing you get.
Ask Silvia for the low carb options! There's a hidden menu they got!

Had food delivered to go from grub hub. Ordered street tacos with 1st taco pork and pineapple and 2nd taco fried pork. It was bland and tasted old. The churros was fried in old oil. I lived in San Antonio, TX and this is not authentic Mexican food.

I do not eat meat. So i ordered vegetable fajitas for pick up. What i got was vegetables and nothing else. No rice, no tortillas. ( were they forgotten? ) Taste was oily, fatty. Portion was small.  I wanted to like this place so much, but it was a disappointment.
Shrimp Tacos and margaritas were amazing! At night, the outdoor lighting coupled with the music create a great atmosphere!!

My first time there.  The drinks and tacos were great. I loved the atmosphere and vibes with the staff and location..  I will definitely come back there again.

The food is great. Definitely nothing to complain there. The tacos are scrumptious, and the churros make my mouth water. However, the way that they are handling covid-19 is unacceptable. The outdoor seating is picnic tables right next to each other and the workers and customers aren’t wearing masks. That means there is no social distancing or mask wearing. Even if just the waiters wore masks it would make a huge difference. But it’s great for takeout.
Excellent autentic Mexican Food!
Margaritas are to die for! The food could be better.

Delicious and authentic food with a flexible chef and staff who changed recipes around for strict vegetarians. Of note, their mole has chicken stock while their black beans are veg friendly (other beans are cooked in lard). Their cactus salad, although authentic, is not a salad in the traditional sense, and does not suffice for a meal.
Great food and price for delivery, def way better than Guapos which has gotten worse for delivery quality and recent use of aluminum togo packaging
Amazing Tacos and Churros!!
It was a cute little place. Loved the atmosphere and the service.

I'm always cautious with Mexican places in the DMV area since I'm from Texas and know what it's actually supposed to taste like. Casa Oaxaca is legit and delicious. Tacos are great, mole is spot-on, margaritas are extremely satisfying. Their tres leches cake is the best I've had in the area: flavorful and super moist with sweet milk seeping out of the cake when you dig the spoon in, as it should be. I haven't had a single bad experience here.  Their outdoor seating area is perfect for pandemic eating. We live across the street and this is actually the first place we ate at after three months of takeout only.  TLDR: Great food. Eat here.
Excellent quality food and great service. The house salsa is one of the best I’ve ever had.

First visit was during quarantine and they have a nice set up outside with fresh food and nice variety of drinks. With seating being limited, we were fortunate enough to get reservations. The hibiscus margarita is by far my favorite but they have so many to choose from home. The fresh chips and salsa, hold you over perfectly till your appetizers and main meals come. The tacos couldn’t be any better! So many options and the presentation is neat, attractive and fresh. Looking forward to going back because we love tacos!!

The service was bad. The server was pushing as to order more. When we ordered pina colada they gave us with absolutely no liquor in it. When we asked she told us the bartender is new sorry. We live next door, we probably won’t return again. I don’t recommend this place.

I absolutely loved their pina colada that came in a pineapple, this I think is a new addition to their menu. I ordered al pastor and lengua tacos. I've had better but these are also good! They are a bit pricey and their taco are regular sized. Their esquite is very good I definitely recommend trying that. I also had their tamarind margarita and its delicious! Overall I liked this place just thought it was a bit pricy, you are in Bethesda though so that's expected.
Wrong order after waiting 2h

We go to this place often, but I think it's important for them to know how poor the service was on May 5th. Yes, I know everyone was ordering Mexican food on this day most likely. We put in an order at 5:45 by 8:15 we had still not received our order not would the place answer their phone. I most nights I would give them a high grade on this night they get a well deserved F.

First-rate vibes and super attentive service. The menu was fresh and delightful. Will absolutely recommend this spot to friends and family. Affordable prices and large portions. Keep up the great work.

We enjoy eating out. Yesterday we came to this fine place which friends told us about. We enjoyed a lovely time there with great dishes and a well-trained team and an impressive  cuisine. We put this place in our phone list  and we will definitely return soon. We warmly recommend.

Out standing staff, customer service, and amazing food! Absolutely love the restaurant decor, outdoor patio and outdoor bar has a great atmosphere. Love going there after work for a few drinks. The owners Raquel and Marco are very kind.
Great drinks. Tried the grasshopper tacos 🦗
The best and authentic Mexican-Oaxacan food. The tacos of grasshopper are the best! Also the Mole! And the margaritas are the best.

Casa Oaxaca is by far the best Mexican restaurant in DC offering authentic food from Oaxaca.  The atmosphere and outdoor patio are simply gorgeous.  The quality of the food is amazing and the service is incredible. My family and I always enjoy eating here.  I particularly recommend their chapulines, tacos de lengua, tostada de ceviche, esquites and micheladas. Simply a must!!

The food is delicious!!! They have the best Guacamole in the area. Staff is beyond friendly. I had the coconut margarita, very natural flavors, no artificial flavors. Great location, parking is convenient. Highly recommend for any occasion, can’t wait to go back this Friday for happy hour! Check out their Instagram page for daily updates.
Great food , great Environment, Great Service!! Best Authentic Mexican food in Bethesda definitely recommend Casa Oaxaca to all my friends and Family

If your looking to have a family dinner, special datenight , or even a girls night out with great authentic Mexican food  and flavor-able drinks this is the place to go 💃 I’ve been too several Mexican restaurants in the DMV but this place is my absolute favorite.  Customer service is always outstanding and atmosphere is amazing!! Really good authentic Mexican food. Everyone was personal and made you feel welcome. The chef even came out to talk with us. I will definitely be back and try the tlayuda. It is not on the menu but the chef said he can make it

Love this spot! The outdoor area is perfect for warm evenings, the margaritas are tasty (and they will make them with mezcal if you ask), and the Oaxacan cheese in the quesadillas and queso fundido is beyond delicious. Servers are always friendly and we've already become regulars. Hoping this place puts down roots - definitely a new fave. Only drawback is that the tacos are on the small side for the price. Otherwise a great spot.
If you like to be greeted, questions answered, treated with respect and experience a good time then DO NOT come here.

Wow... I hope the owners reach out to me as soon as possible. The woman that answered the phone was extremely rude and then when I spoke with the manager and asked for both their names she hung up on me!!! When I visited this place in the past all the employees were excellent but after this I wouldn't recommend this place to anyone. Why would you think you could treat people like that? This place needs better training and new people, get rid of the 2 women that clearly have issues with providing good customer service.

This small and lively place is an excellent addition to  Bethesda. Not a lot of indoor seating but high ceilings That get pretty noisy when the crowd gets going.. lots of outside seating when the weather is right. The portions are not large so order enough to not leave hungry and enjoy the 1st salsa because any additional sauce and chips or tortillas cost $3 extra. They may or may not tell you this surcharge when you request these refills.  Fajitas  and enchiladas were very good.  Service was outstanding.
Great food. One of the better authentic Mexican food places around.
Chile relleno, Chicken fajitas & churros. Everything was delicious
Nice atmosphere at the outdoor terrace. Great variety of interesting and atypical Mexican food. Cheerful and attentive and efficient service staff. Unlike the price, the Margaritas are weak.
Wonderful,  great food, comfortable outside seating. Charming staff.

My friends had their sisters 33rd birthday here and it turned out fantastic ! The ambiance and the food were amazing . They have inside and outside seating . The outside seating has gravel and picnic tables accompanied with an outside bar under a shaded area which gives everything an at home vibe . We had the pleasure of meeting the owner who is also the chef and his colleagues ! It was an amazing turn out with amazing tasty food !

The tacos are wonderful! I had the Al Pastor and La Lengua which were both tasty. The spicy strawberry margarita was also delicious -- I've had it twice now, and one time was very spicy while the other was mild. I wonder if you could ask for a certain spice level? Regardless, you should get tacos here! Try some mezcal for a little smokiness while you're at it. 👍

3 Stars for a beautiful outdoor atmosphere and their mojito was good, they need to serve more than just bacardi... will not be going back for the food. 2 stars for the food, it wasn't bad but it wasn't good. The server must have been new she struggled to answer our questions, then the queso we ordered came out the same tine as our meals and we were asked what we wanted first... huh?  First time there and nothing grabbed our bellies attention. The queso was not what we were hoping it would be, the consistency was that of melted marshmallow and didn't have much flavor. It was just weird. They brought out soft tortillas for us to scoop the queso with , got that pictured? We asked for chips and she said it would be an extra cost... The tacos are micro mini in size, and the enchilada mole meal didn't have much flavor other than the overbearing dark sauce on it. Should have been smothered in melted cheese and flavors of cilantro etc. Not the case. Oh and sour cream is 2 dollars extra. C'mon really?  Disappointed, it's a cute place to sit outside but there are better places to eat. :/
The best tacos in Bethesda!

Second time eating here and I was hoping for the best. It's such a great space but the food is not good at all.  The servers are really great however and I hope they can pull it together.  It's hard to find great street tacos.

Excellent. Amazing service inside, and I'll try the outside patio bar next time. Mezcal "el silencio" was amazingly smooth. My wife lived the mixed cocktails. Tacos with handmade tortillas, and they were tasty.

Five stars for service. We arrived for happy hour when we were told we had to sit close to the bar on the patio. Empty plates don't stay on the table, and one of the chefs presented a grasshopper taco personally. It was about the size of a dollar bill, and it was delicious. The chicken tamale was too.  The drink menu featured exotic flavors like tamarind and sorrel. Everyone in my party really liked how the drinks were crafted. (I could have used more triple sec.) The prices were a little high, but you won't find a restaurant like this anywhere else in the area.
Awesome place. Good drinks (spicy🍍 margarita) and tacos. Have had the mole previously too.
Great patio and very good food.
Some of the beast drinks in Bethesda and their tacos are as close to authentic as they come.  One of my favorite spots in Bethesda.
The staff (particularly Ishmael) went out of their way to make sure our group had a great dining experience.  We enjoyed the drinks and the food (from tacos to grasshoppers) on the comfortable patio.
Great atmosphere and friendly staff. Although they seemed over loaded at times. The food is good, not bad but not great either.
Delicious eats. Affordable prices. Great atmosphere. I will definitely go back!!

A low key place for strong mezcal and tequila based drinks. I highly recommend the El Camino. For top shelf drinks, they have Don Julio, as well.  They have not invested in environment or ambiance in the interior of the restaurant However, they have an awesome little alcohol garden which can be enjoyed in the warmer months.  They have good, but we focused on the drinks.  Enjoy!
The bartender was wonderful, attentive and provided great recommendations
The atmosphere is great.  Service was wonderful like the food

Stopped by for drinks after getting dinner in DC. Inside bar was full and the host was too busy chatting with a friend to really notice us and point out the second bar in the patio. After we found it, we were very impressed with the ambiance, drinks, and especially our new friend behind the bar, Nahu. The house chips and salsa were excellent and after a few rounds of drinks, we gave in and ordered a piece of tres leches cake. If those two are any indication of the rest of the menu, we are already excited about our next visit for dinner (and more margaritas!)
Love this place, many taco options
We loved the outdoor patio, but like most outdoor seating in the area it definitely can be busy on a beautiful day.
Probably the most authentic Mexican food in Bethesda.

Chips and salsa were good: salsa is fresh and chips didn't taste like they were out of a bag like some restaurants. Mole enchiladas were very good: more of a tomato-y mole in Oaxacan style as opposed to the darker brown, sweeter ones I'm used to but very good flavor. Black beans are good tasting as well as the rice, which wasn't too dry like some places.  Solid Mexican food, definitely will go back.
Good cocktails, but a little pricey, even for Happy Hour!  Guac and chips are excellent, and some bartenders (especially Irene) are awesome!
Great food and drinks. Outdoor patio is the place to be.

Food was good, the service was real good.
Great outdoor patio with excellent happy hour from 3-7PM daily. Tacos are good but on the smaller side. Really good house chips and salsa. Friendly service
